title: Rodemi
author: Rodemi
content: Hi guys, I have an Innosilicon t2t model and when I connect the miner to the power supply it doesn't work. But when there is only one board, it shows that it run normally, I want to know how to solve this problem? Please help.

comments.author: BitMaxz
comments.body: What do you mean it doesn't work? Do you mean the miner is running but not mining or no hashrate?To troubleshoot your problem you must post the whole logs here and don't forget to put them inside the code tag or use pastebin.com and share it here.Also, read the common problems and solutions from Innosilicon support.

comments.author: GFDhd
comments.body: Do you have another power supply? You can try other power supply to see if it can run.

comments.author: Rodemi
comments.body: I gave a new PSU and the machine started running fine until now. This is great.
